CAPE TOWN - Western Cape Police say they're making progress in reducing the number of illegal firearms that are circulating in gang hotspots. More than 180 guns have been seized over the last five weeks. The police's Andre Traut said: “During the period of 22 February and 26 March this year, a total of 186 firearms and 3,058 rounds of ammunition have been confiscated from 147 suspects who are now paying the price for criminal behaviour.” Download the Eyewitness News app to your iOS  or Android device.